<subSubSection id="C3126565FF86FFA1FF0BF860FE92A7F9" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736EEFF86FFA1FF0BF860FE92A7F9" blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF86FFA1FF0BF860FEC5A782" bold="true" box="[197,344,1941,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the metasternum yellow with two wide black stripes joined anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF776666FF87FFA0FF59F868FBD6A7D8" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198042/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="19" targetBox="[294,1298,205,1933]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BB736EEFF87FFA0FF59F868FBD6A7D8" blockId="5.[151,1437,1949,2037]" pageId="5" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF87FFA0FF59F868FEC8A798" bold="true" box="[151,341,1949,1973]" pageId="5" pageNumber="19">FIGURES 8–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C084D6DFF87FFA0FE92F86BFDB8A798" box="[348,549,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Systropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coalitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF87FFA0FE92F86BFDB8A798" box="[348,549,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="19">Systropus coalitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
