</taxonomicNameLabel>
8. Male genitalia, posterior view; 9. epandrium, cercus and sternite 10, ventral view; 10–11. gonocoxite and gonostylus, ventral and lateral views; 12–13. phallus, dorsal and lateral views. Female. 14. Apical portion of sternite 8, ventral view; 15. apex of abdomen, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3126565FF84FFA3FF0BFF62FF7EA16A" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736EEFF84FFA3FF0BFF62FF7EA16A" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF84FFA3FF0BFF62FEA3A09C" bold="true" box="[197,318,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D6DFF84FFA3FCD6FF6DFBC3A09F" authority="Enderlein, 1926" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1926" box="[792,1118,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Systropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF84FFA3FCD6FF6DFC14A09C" box="[792,905,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">S. excisus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B1FFF84FFA3FC56FF6DFBCBA09F" author="Enderlein" box="[920,1110,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" refString="Enderlein, G. (1926) Zur Kenntnis der Bombyliiden-Subfamilie Systropodinae (Dipt.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 43, 69 - 92." type="journal article" year="1926">
Enderlein, 
<number id="3DC024C9FF84FFA3FBD4FF6DFBCBA09F" box="[1050,1110,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F31F767EFF84FFA3FB6AFF6DFB77A09F" box="[1188,1258,152,178]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">China</collectingCountry>
(Gangdong) in having similar antennal coloration, but it can be separated from the latter by the apex of the hind tibia yellow and the metasternum yellow with two wide black stripes joined anteriorly. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D6DFF84FFA3FBE3FF17FB3DA0D6" box="[1069,1184,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Systropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excisus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF84FFA3FBE3FF17FB3DA0D6" box="[1069,1184,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">S. excisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apex of the hind tibia is black; the metasternum is yellow with two wide black stripes not joined anteriorly (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B1FFF84FFA3FB2EFEFDFF4BA16A" author="Nagatomi" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" refString="Nagatomi, A., Liu, N. W., Tamaki, N. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (1991) The genus Systropus from Japan, Korea, Taiwan and Thailand (Diptera, Bombyliidae). South Pacific Study, 12 (1), 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1991">
Nagatomi 
<emphasis id="B97CEAFCFF84FFA3FA91FEFDFA01A10C" box="[1375,1436,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="3DC024C9FF84FFA3FF59FED8FF4BA16A" box="[151,214,301,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="20" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
